00:00:03.789 --> 00:00:09.161
Namaste, I'm Lata Jain,
Welcome to Lata's Kitchen

00:00:09.375 --> 00:00:13.878
We can make many dishes with potatoes

00:00:13.878 --> 00:00:17.891
Dum Aloo is a very delicious party dish

00:00:17.891 --> 00:00:26.523
Today I'm going to make Dum Aloo, Lets see
the ingredients required for making this

00:00:26.641 --> 00:00:32.947
Potatoes - 4 medium sized, 
washed, peeled and cut into fours

00:00:33.164 --> 00:00:35.234
Tomatoes - 3

00:00:35.469 --> 00:00:37.539
Yogurt - 1/2 cup

00:00:37.539 --> 00:00:39.618
Oil - 3 tbsp

00:00:39.668 --> 00:00:45.234
Watermelon seeds - 2 tbsp,
soaked in water for 3 hrs

00:00:45.472 --> 00:00:47.611
Cumin seeds - 1/2 tsp

00:00:47.611 --> 00:00:49.524
Asafoetida - 2 pinch

00:00:49.524 --> 00:00:52.766
Ginger - 1 inch piece, grated

00:00:52.766 --> 00:00:55.492
Green Chillies - 2, cut lengthwise

00:00:55.492 --> 00:00:58.603
Dry Fenugreek Leaves - 2 tsp

00:00:58.703 --> 00:01:01.936
Paprika (Kashmiri Mirch/Degi Mirch) - 1/2 tsp

00:01:01.986 --> 00:01:05.598
Salt - 1 tsp, adjust to taste

00:01:05.598 --> 00:01:08.715
Garam Masala - 1 tsp

00:01:08.715 --> 00:01:12.123
Turmeric Powder - 1/4 tsp

00:01:12.173 --> 00:01:14.912
Coriander Powder - 1/4 tsp

00:01:14.912 --> 00:01:17.875
Cilantro - 2 tbsp, chopped

00:01:17.875 --> 00:01:20.501
Oil for frying Potatoes

00:01:20.501 --> 00:01:23.853
Lets start making Dum Aloo

00:01:23.853 --> 00:01:29.407
First we'll deep fry the potatoes

00:01:29.492 --> 00:01:32.790
Heat oil in a wok

00:01:33.398 --> 00:01:44.446
Oil is heated, Turn gas
to low, and add potatoes

00:01:51.758 --> 00:01:57.734
Fry on low heat till they are golden brown

00:01:57.773 --> 00:02:07.383
In the meanwhile, we'll blend tomatoes
and watermelon seeds for gravy

00:02:07.523 --> 00:02:16.625
Add tomatoes and watermelon seeds to the
blender jar and blend into a fine paste

00:02:18.500 --> 00:02:22.497
Flip the potatoes often

00:02:26.727 --> 00:02:33.133
Paste for gravy is ready,
take it out in a bowl

00:02:34.383 --> 00:02:39.265
Potatoes should be crisp
outside and soft inside

00:02:44.422 --> 00:02:48.095
They are getting golden brown

00:02:52.452 --> 00:02:57.664
They have turned golden brown, now
take them out on a paper towel

00:03:09.594 --> 00:03:12.609
Now we'll prepare gravy for dum aloo

00:03:13.898 --> 00:03:19.680
Heat oil in a wok

00:03:20.383 --> 00:03:24.022
Oil is heated, now add the cumin seeds

00:03:26.984 --> 00:03:28.357
Add asafoetida

00:03:30.070 --> 00:03:32.254
Add paprika

00:03:35.430 --> 00:03:37.438
Add ginger

00:03:41.289 --> 00:03:43.371
Add green chillies

00:03:44.753 --> 00:03:47.023
Add tomato paste

00:03:56.516 --> 00:03:59.104
Saute this paste

00:04:04.484 --> 00:04:06.532
Add turmeric powder

00:04:13.000 --> 00:04:15.553
Add Coriander powder

00:04:21.758 --> 00:04:25.628
Cook untill oil starts to separate

00:04:29.141 --> 00:04:36.713
Watermelon seeds gives a very nice
texture to the gravy,

00:04:36.739 --> 00:04:43.634
You can also use khas khas
instead of watermelon seeds

00:04:45.297 --> 00:04:51.091
Oil has started to separate
out, add dry fenugreek leaves

00:04:54.914 --> 00:04:57.839
Add yogurt

00:05:04.102 --> 00:05:08.342
Cook it for few minutes

00:05:13.547 --> 00:05:19.113
Oil has separated out, now add garam masala

00:05:24.172 --> 00:05:26.745
Add salt

00:05:31.281 --> 00:05:39.635
Add about 1 cup of water

00:05:43.875 --> 00:05:46.843
Cook it for 2 minutes

00:05:47.453 --> 00:05:52.791
Turn gas to low and add
fried potatoes to the gravy

00:06:00.469 --> 00:06:08.160
Cook it for about 5 minutes

00:06:10.664 --> 00:06:19.500
Dum aloo are ready, turn off
the gas, garnish with cilantro

00:06:23.281 --> 00:06:26.641
Take out into a serving bowl

00:06:33.164 --> 00:06:35.378
Dum Aloo are ready

00:06:35.378 --> 00:06:38.235
These are very tasty

00:06:38.235 --> 00:06:44.407
You can serve it with naan,
roti, paratha or puri

00:06:44.407 --> 00:06:47.395
Thanks for watching Dum Aloo

